MemberSignature.Value: public: property System::Byte WADMIN_DEFAULT_TRACKING_METHOD { System::Byte get(); void set(System::Byte value); };
member this.WADMIN_DEFAULT_TRACKING_METHOD : byte with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies the default method for reporting progress on tasks.

remarks.para: The default value of WADMIN_DEFAULT_TRACKING_METHOD is 2 (percent complete). You can set this value in the Tracking Method section of the Task Settings and Display page in Project Web App (http://ServerName/ProjectServerName/_layouts/pwa/Admin/Statusing.aspx).

item.description: Hours per period (for example, hours per day) of work done on a task.
Total hours of actual work done and work remaining on each task period.

remarks.para: The enterprise global template determines the default tracking method for new projects.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property bool WADMIN_IS_TRACKING_METHOD_LOCKED { bool get(); void set(bool value); };
member this.WADMIN_IS_TRACKING_METHOD_LOCKED : bool with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies whether to force project managers to use the progress reporting method that is set by WADMIN_DEFAULT_TRACKING_METHOD.

remarks.para: You can set the value of WADMIN_IS_TRACKING_METHOD_LOCKED by selecting the check box in the Tracking Method section of the Task Settings and Display page in Project Web App (http://ServerName/ProjectServerName/_layouts/pwa/Admin/Statusing.aspx).

MemberSignature.Value: public: property System::Byte WADMIN_PROTECT_ACTUALS { System::Byte get(); void set(System::Byte value); };
member this.WADMIN_PROTECT_ACTUALS : byte with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies whether work actuals are protected.

remarks.para: The default value of WADMIN_PROTECT_ACTUALS is 0 (the check box is cleared; actuals are not protected). You can set this value in the Protect User Updates section of the Task Settings and Display page in Project Web App (http://ServerName/ProjectServerName/_layouts/pwa/Admin/Statusing.aspx).

item.description: Allow the project manager to modify work actuals.
Restrict updates to Project Web App.

remarks.para: The My Tasks page in Project Web App shows tasks that are currently in progress and tasks that are scheduled to start within the number of days specified by WADMIN_STAT_LOOK_AHEAD.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property bool WADMIN_STAT_TIMESHEET_TIED { bool get(); void set(bool value); };
member this.WADMIN_STAT_TIMESHEET_TIED : bool with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies whether users must report time only on the timesheet, and then synchronize task status with the timesheet.

remarks.para: The default value of WADMIN_STAT_TIMESHEET_TIED is false (the check box is cleared; users can report time on both the timesheet and on the task status pages). You can set this value in the Protect User Updates section of the Task Settings and Display page in Project Web App (http://ServerName/ProjectServerName/_layouts/pwa/Admin/Statusing.aspx).

item.description: Allow users to report time on both the timesheet and on the task status pages.
Users report time only on the timesheet, and then synchronize task status with the timesheet.

Docs.summary: Specifies whether resources report hours worked per day or total hours per week.

remarks.para: The default value of WADMIN_TS_DEF_ENTRY_MODE_ENUM is 0 (hours per day). You can set this value in the Reporting Display section of the Task Settings and Display page in Project Web App (http://ServerName/ProjectServerName/_layouts/pwa/Admin/Statusing.aspx).

item.description: Report hours per day of work done on a task.
Report total hours per week of work done on a task.
